article.headline: Koehn hits five 3s and scores 19 to lead Wildcats
article.linkText: Wecker injured in K-State rout of New Hampshire
article.story:
MANHATTAN, Kan. (AP) -- Laurie Koehn hit five 3-pointers and scored 19 points to lead Kansas State (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 19 AP) to an 84-50 victory over New Hampshire on Friday in the first round of the Wildcat Classic.

Claire Coggins added a career-high 14 points and Megan Mahoney 11 for Kansas State, which used a 15-2 run early in the second half to build a 63-35 lead.

Kendra Wecker scored seven of Kansas State's first 14 points but landed awkwardly on her left foot after a jump shot 4:21 into the game. The preseason All-American, averaging 24 points, left Bramlage Coliseum on crutches.

Kansas State (4-1) bolted to a 16-0 lead, but after Wecker left, Kansas State only outscored its opponent by three points for a 45-28 halftime lead.

Ashley Cerniglia lead New Hampshire (1-3) with nine points.

Kansas State will play Liberty on Saturday in the tournament's championship game. The Flames defeated Tennessee State 74-38 in the opener.
